      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Briefly disabling cancelability is useful"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "if a thread performs some critical action"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "that must not be interrupted by a cancellation request."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Beware of disabling cancelability for long periods,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "or around operations that may block for long periods,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "since that will render the thread unresponsive to cancellation requests."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SS",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " Asynchronous cancelability"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Setting the cancelability type to"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".B",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " PTHREAD_CANCEL_ASYNCHRONOUS"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "is rarely useful."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Since the thread could be canceled at"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".I",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " any"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "time, it cannot safely reserve resources (e.g., allocating memory with"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " malloc (3)),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "acquire mutexes, semaphores, or locks, and so on."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Reserving resources is unsafe because the application has no way of"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "knowing what the state of these resources is when the thread is canceled;"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "that is, did cancellation occur before the resources were reserved,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "while they were reserved, or after they were released?"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Furthermore, some internal data structures"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(e.g., the linked list of free blocks managed by the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " malloc (3)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "family of functions) may be left in an inconsistent state"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "if cancellation occurs in the middle of the function call."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Consequently, clean-up handlers cease to be useful."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
